;AMINO GROUP (NH2): STAPLED PEPTIDE IS AMIDATED AT THE
 C-TERMINUS.
ACETYL GROUP (ACE): STAPLED PEPTIDE IS ACETYLATED AT THE
 N-TERMINUS.
2 (R)-2-(4'-PENTENYL)ALANINE (2JN): THIS NON-NATURAL AMINO
 ACID FORMS A COVALENT BOND BETWEEN RESIDUES 20 AND 24
;
_pdbx_entry_details.sequence_details
;E69 AND K70 ARE MUTATED TO ALANINES FOR SURFACE ENTROPY
REDUCTION. THE GPLGS OF THE CRYSTALLISATION CONSTRUCT IS
AN ARTEFACT OF OUR CLONING AND PURIFICATION STRATEGIES.
THIS STAPLED PEPTIDE WAS ORIGINALLY BASED ON A P53 PEPTIDE
BUT IS NOW SO HEAVILY MODIFIED SO AS TO BEAR LITTLE
RESEMBLANCE TO THE ORIGINAL SEQUENCE.
;
